There's problems with that. Charcoal burners in the past knew how to make all kinds of different 'types' of charcoal with different burning methods to create different grades for different purposes. Creating the right kind of charcoal for weapons-grade blackpowder requires a lot of know-how, and even certain types of wood. It could happen over time, but it'll take a long time before a lot of effort trying to create even rudimentary black powder weaponry bares much fruit. Piracy =/= theft. The "Piracy is theft" slogan was made up by corporations that feared home taping would destroy their industry, and they were so stubborn that if not for Steve Jobs the music industry would've imploded post-Napster.
